WEBVTT

00:01.960 --> 00:05.214
NARRATOR:
In a land of myth and a time of magic...

00:05.380 --> 00:10.260
...the destiny of a great kingdom
rests on the shoulders of a young man.

00:10.636 --> 00:13.889
His name: Merlin.

00:16.767 --> 00:18.101
It's time.

00:20.312 --> 00:23.732
Sire, we're under attack!
They're within the city walls.

00:23.899 --> 00:26.318
All quarters of Camelot
are now under our control.

00:27.319 --> 00:28.695
ARTHUR:
Agravaine.

00:28.862 --> 00:31.281
They're coming for Arthur.
If they find him, they'll kill him.

00:31.448 --> 00:34.451
ELYAN: We have to make it across the border,
find sanctuary anywhere we can.

00:35.285 --> 00:37.871
You're smugglers?
If you're caught, you could be killed.

00:38.038 --> 00:41.124
Tristan and Isolde? I don't think so.

00:43.293 --> 00:46.338
-Who the hell are you?
-My name is Arthur Pendragon.

00:47.714 --> 00:50.509
We had a deal.
Partners for life, remember?

00:50.676 --> 00:53.178
-Guinevere.
-Hello, Arthur.

00:55.055 --> 00:56.598
AGRAVAINE:
Ensure the village is surrounded.

00:56.765 --> 00:58.225
No one must escape.

00:58.433 --> 00:59.560
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

00:59.726 --> 01:03.397
Agravaine. He's found us.

01:49.651 --> 01:52.446
MERLIN:
I'll cover our tracks. You keep going.

01:56.783 --> 02:00.412
[SPEAKING IN ANCIENT LANGUAGE]

02:15.844 --> 02:17.679
[CREATURE SCREECHES]

02:21.767 --> 02:23.226
Take cover!

02:30.525 --> 02:32.152
[SCREAMING]

02:33.528 --> 02:34.696
ARTHUR:
Did you lose them?

02:34.863 --> 02:36.615
-We're safe.
-You're sure?

02:36.782 --> 02:38.617
-Do I look like an idiot?
-Yes.

02:38.784 --> 02:40.869
He doesn't change,
does he?

02:42.079 --> 02:43.538
Which way now?

02:45.832 --> 02:47.668
| thought you said you grew up
in these tunnels.

02:47.834 --> 02:49.503
| did. It could be that way.

02:49.670 --> 02:52.047
-Or it could be that way.
-Yes.

02:52.214 --> 02:54.091
That's very reassuring.

02:56.718 --> 02:58.720
[MEN GROANING]

03:01.682 --> 03:04.267
[CREATURE SCREECHES]

03:06.561 --> 03:08.271
Run!

03:25.580 --> 03:27.582
TRISTAN:
So you know Arthur?

03:27.749 --> 03:30.085
GWEN:
| was a servant in Camelot.

03:30.252 --> 03:32.838
-To Arthur?
-No.

03:33.046 --> 03:34.840
So why are you here?

03:35.382 --> 03:36.925
He's my king.

03:37.342 --> 03:39.803
Can't say I've detected
many kingly qualities so far.

03:40.220 --> 03:41.930
GWEN:
Well, maybe you don't know him.

03:49.312 --> 03:50.647
[CLATTERING IN DISTANCE]

03:50.814 --> 03:52.107
Shh!

03:59.156 --> 04:00.657
[CLATTERING]

04:03.452 --> 04:05.412
| thought you said
we'd lost them.

04:05.579 --> 04:06.788
| thought I had.

04:06.955 --> 04:08.915
It won't take long
for them to catch us.

04:09.082 --> 04:11.042
-I'll go back.
-What are you going to do?

04:11.209 --> 04:12.919
MERLIN: Create a diversion.
-It's too risky.

04:13.086 --> 04:15.464
| know these tunnels.
Agravaine doesn't. You keep going.

04:15.630 --> 04:16.964
Merlin.

04:19.676 --> 04:21.136
Don't do anything stupid.

04:21.970 --> 04:23.305
Me?

04:33.565 --> 04:35.108
[CLATTERING]

04:44.576 --> 04:46.077
Oh, hello!

04:54.711 --> 04:56.171
AGRAVAINE:
Merlin!

04:58.840 --> 05:00.258
Merlin.

05:08.016 --> 05:09.267
Where's Arthur?

05:10.101 --> 05:11.520
Be careful.

05:13.104 --> 05:14.773
What are you talking about?

05:15.232 --> 05:17.025
Where's Arthur?

05:19.027 --> 05:21.780
Tell me. Now.

05:23.365 --> 05:24.533
Or I'll have to kill you.

05:28.870 --> 05:30.413
| don't think so.

05:30.580 --> 05:32.040
Ah.

05:42.300 --> 05:44.344
[COUGHS THEN GASPING]

05:56.189 --> 05:57.315
You have magic.

05:58.692 --> 06:00.402
| was born with it.

06:02.904 --> 06:04.614
So it's you.

06:05.907 --> 06:07.325
You're Emrys.

06:09.536 --> 06:11.997
That is what the druids call me.

06:13.498 --> 06:16.710
And you've been at court
all this time, eh?

06:19.671 --> 06:21.298
At Arthur's side.

06:21.464 --> 06:22.507
[CHUCKLES]

06:23.091 --> 06:26.094
How you've managed
to deceive him. Ha, ha.

06:26.678 --> 06:29.014
| am impressed, Merlin.

06:30.265 --> 06:33.059
Perhaps we're more alike than you think.

06:46.323 --> 06:47.699
[SHOUTS]

07:29.240 --> 07:30.867
TRISTAN: What are you doing?
-Shh!

07:31.201 --> 07:32.827
[CLATTERING]

07:34.663 --> 07:36.665
-Merlin.
-He knows the tunnels.

07:36.831 --> 07:38.625
-He'll find his way.
-I'm going back.

07:41.127 --> 07:42.796
For a servant?

07:43.254 --> 07:45.048
You're wrong about him.

07:55.809 --> 07:57.143
ARTHUR:
Merlin!

07:58.269 --> 07:59.646
Where have you been?

08:00.563 --> 08:03.608
-Were you worried about me?
-No.

08:05.151 --> 08:07.112
| was making sure
we weren't being followed.

08:07.278 --> 08:08.613
You came back to look for me.

08:10.991 --> 08:12.450
All right. It's true.

08:13.535 --> 08:16.788
| came back because you're the only friend
| have, and I couldn't bear to lose you.

08:19.165 --> 08:22.043
-Really?
-Don't be stupid.

08:33.596 --> 08:35.306
TRISTAN:
So where now?

08:36.850 --> 08:39.144
To the plains
beyond the mountains.

08:39.309 --> 08:40.602
You sure?

08:40.770 --> 08:43.398
That's Lot's kingdom.
He's no friend of the Pendragons.

08:43.732 --> 08:46.901
Well, maybe we could find somewhere
here. A house where we could rest.

08:47.235 --> 08:50.405
We're fugitives,
a danger to anyone who harbors us.

08:50.572 --> 08:54.451
MERLIN: He's right.
We must travel back towards Camelot.

08:54.617 --> 08:57.328
-No. We need to keep going.
-We'll be safe in the Forest of Ascetir.

08:57.495 --> 08:58.913
-At least for a while.
-No.

08:59.080 --> 09:01.916
If anyone has survived this battle,
that's where they'll be hiding.

09:02.083 --> 09:03.668
TRISTAN:
| know which I'd do.

09:03.835 --> 09:06.796
You're the king, Arthur.
You're our leader.

09:06.963 --> 09:10.341
All right.
Forest of Ascetir it is.

09:20.977 --> 09:22.896
[BELLS TOLLING]

09:25.690 --> 09:28.193
Come on, Gaius. Hold fast.

09:28.401 --> 09:30.361
[KEYS JANGLING]

09:30.820 --> 09:32.739
[DOOR OPENS]

09:37.035 --> 09:38.286
[GRUNTS]

09:38.453 --> 09:41.247
Don't worry.
At least we'll get to eat.

09:52.258 --> 09:55.011
So you've had a chance
to sing for your supper.

09:57.138 --> 09:59.933
| thought I might make it
a little harder this time.

10:00.225 --> 10:01.935
Seems fair.

10:03.269 --> 10:06.356
<i>Oh, but you can't fight
with your bare hands.</i>

10:09.025 --> 10:10.860
Never mind.

10:11.027 --> 10:14.030
You're a knight of Camelot.
You'll be fine.

10:21.204 --> 10:22.831
[MEN CLAMORING]

10:24.457 --> 10:25.834
What the hell.

10:35.635 --> 10:37.303
Well, well, well. Look at you.

10:38.429 --> 10:42.475
First you go back to rescue your servant.
Now you're getting your hands dirty.

10:42.642 --> 10:46.146
But then again,
why shouldn't you?

10:46.771 --> 10:48.439
You're just like everyone else.

10:48.606 --> 10:50.567
There's nothing special about you,
is there?

10:50.733 --> 10:52.777
Maybe you're right.
Maybe I don't deserve to be king.

10:52.944 --> 10:55.572
Well, that's all right,
because you're not.

10:56.239 --> 10:57.740
Not anymore.

11:09.502 --> 11:11.421
[THUNDER RUMBLES]

11:18.803 --> 11:22.098
-Arthur? Arthur.
-Don't.

11:24.851 --> 11:27.020
What happened in Ealdor
was a moment's weakness.

11:29.397 --> 11:30.481
What you did to me--

11:33.443 --> 11:36.905
Everything I cherished between us,
everything we had, it's gone.

11:40.325 --> 11:41.784
And it'll never change.

11:44.454 --> 11:45.997
I'm sorry.

12:02.263 --> 12:03.932
Enjoy your supper.

12:06.392 --> 12:08.269
For it will be your last.

12:20.240 --> 12:22.200
You need to eat.

12:22.367 --> 12:24.744
Whether I eat or not...

12:25.620 --> 12:27.413
...I'm not long for this world.

12:27.580 --> 12:28.873
Come on, Gaius.

12:30.375 --> 12:33.211
I'm a physician, Elyan.

12:34.128 --> 12:37.757
| spent my days
watching the cycle of life.

12:38.716 --> 12:41.594
If there's one thing I'm not afraid of,
it's death.

12:43.179 --> 12:45.139
Don't waste your food.

12:46.182 --> 12:48.559
If Gwaine has to fight again...

12:49.477 --> 12:52.480
...he'll need all the strength he can get.

13:06.160 --> 13:08.538
Come on. I'll take watch.

13:14.085 --> 13:15.962
Arthur, what's the matter?

13:19.799 --> 13:22.427
Don't listen to Tristan.
He doesn't know you.

13:27.557 --> 13:29.058
| trusted the wrong people.

13:30.518 --> 13:32.979
They betrayed you. That wasn't your fault.

13:33.146 --> 13:35.648
No. I was a fool.

13:38.276 --> 13:39.527
| misjudged everyone.

13:42.280 --> 13:43.865
My uncle.

13:44.574 --> 13:46.117
Morgana.

13:48.703 --> 13:51.164
Every decision I've made has been wrong.

13:51.706 --> 13:56.502
-You're being too hard on yourself.
- I should be more discerning, wise.

13:57.628 --> 13:59.547
A statesman, a king.

14:00.089 --> 14:03.343
Tristan's right.
There's nothing special about me.

14:05.178 --> 14:07.055
-I'm just like everyone else.
-You're not.

14:08.639 --> 14:11.267
-You're a worthy king.
-I'm good with a sword.

14:14.187 --> 14:15.938
-That's all.
-Your people love you.

14:16.105 --> 14:17.357
Most of them are dead...

14:19.317 --> 14:22.111
-...thanks to me.
-No. Most of them escaped.

14:22.278 --> 14:24.822
And they'll be here in the forest.
I'm sure of that.

14:25.239 --> 14:27.617
If they are, they'll have
to find themselves a new king.

14:32.121 --> 14:33.623
Arthur.

14:34.957 --> 14:36.501
Arthur.

14:43.758 --> 14:46.594
[SHOUTING IN ANCIENT LANGUAGE]

14:55.645 --> 14:57.814
Well, thank you. You saved us all.

14:57.980 --> 15:03.152
The land of Albion and the future
we have all fought for was in peril.

15:06.197 --> 15:08.533
What is troubling you, young warlock?

15:09.784 --> 15:13.079
It's Arthur. He's lost the will to fight.

15:13.246 --> 15:16.833
He feels he's failed his people.
He believes he no longer deserves to be king.

15:17.458 --> 15:21.295
The fate of Camelot rests in your hands,
young warlock.

15:23.047 --> 15:26.050
For you and you alone...

15:26.217 --> 15:29.011
...can restore the king's faith.

15:29.429 --> 15:30.888
How?

15:32.265 --> 15:37.061
You must make him believe
that he can be king once more.

15:48.322 --> 15:51.159
| wish I could be of more help, Merlin.

15:51.826 --> 15:53.369
No.

15:54.245 --> 15:55.746
| know how.

15:56.998 --> 15:59.417
The people who fled Camelot,
do you know where they're hiding?

15:59.584 --> 16:04.422
| am a dragon. I can cover
many leagues in the blink of an eye.

16:05.047 --> 16:07.633
They shouldn't be
too hard to find.

16:08.384 --> 16:10.303
Then we have no time to lose.

16:16.100 --> 16:19.020
-What?
-There's something I need to show you.

16:23.691 --> 16:26.360
This had better be good,
because this really isn't the time...

16:26.527 --> 16:28.446
...for one of your ridiculous games.

16:28.613 --> 16:30.907
| was thinking about last night
and how you were saying...

16:31.073 --> 16:34.076
...how you'd given up all hope, how you were
a poor leader and a shoddy king.

16:34.243 --> 16:35.828
ARTHUR: Shoddy?
-All right. Shabby.

16:35.995 --> 16:37.163
ARTHUR:
Thanks.

16:37.330 --> 16:39.499
Well, it reminded me
of a tale Gaius once told me.

16:40.875 --> 16:45.505
Merlin, I'm really not interested
in your favorite bedtime stories.

16:46.297 --> 16:50.301
For once in your life, just listen.

16:53.346 --> 16:56.849
Many years ago,
before the birth of the five kingdoms...

16:57.016 --> 17:01.521
...this land was in an endless cycle
of bloodshed and war.

17:01.687 --> 17:04.440
But one man was determined
to end all that.

17:05.148 --> 17:08.944
He gathered together the elders of each tribe
and drew up plans for their lands to be divided.

17:09.111 --> 17:10.820
Each would respect
the others' boundaries...

17:10.988 --> 17:12.949
...and rule over the land as they saw fit.

17:13.115 --> 17:15.201
That man was Camelot's first king...

17:15.367 --> 17:18.454
...ancestor to all that followed,
including you, Arthur.

17:19.079 --> 17:21.207
-Bruta.
-You know the story?

17:21.374 --> 17:24.417
Yes. Every child in Camelot does.
Can I go back to bed now?

17:24.585 --> 17:29.090
No, because there's another part
of the story that you haven't heard.

17:29.257 --> 17:32.218
-Really?
-When Bruta was on his deathbed...

17:32.385 --> 17:34.887
...he asked to be taken deep
into the forest.

17:35.054 --> 17:38.057
There, with the last of his strength...

17:38.224 --> 17:40.726
...he thrust his sword into a rock.

17:40.893 --> 17:44.897
If his lineage was ever questioned,
this would form a test.

17:45.064 --> 17:47.775
Only a true king of Camelot
could pull the weapon free.

17:50.319 --> 17:51.862
Are you making this up?

17:53.364 --> 17:55.032
Of course not.

17:58.995 --> 18:00.621
All right.

18:01.789 --> 18:03.666
If it's true,
why haven't I heard this story?

18:03.833 --> 18:07.128
Well, history isn't really
your strong point, is it?

18:08.212 --> 18:09.797
ARTHUR;:
Then where is this rock?

18:09.964 --> 18:13.467
Oh, it was lost many years ago
during the Great Purge.

18:13.634 --> 18:15.136
But...

18:15.761 --> 18:17.346
...I've managed to find it.

18:17.513 --> 18:21.517
I've never heard so much rubbish
in my entire life.

18:21.684 --> 18:25.354
-Are you calling Gaius a liar?
-No. I'm calling you an idiot.

18:25.521 --> 18:27.315
What's that then?

19:11.150 --> 19:12.735
What the hell are you playing at?

19:12.902 --> 19:14.904
I'm proving that you're their leader
and their king.

19:15.071 --> 19:17.073
That sword is stuck fast in solid stone.

19:17.239 --> 19:20.409
-And you're going to pull it out.
-Merlin, it's impossible.

19:20.576 --> 19:22.703
Arthur, you're the true king of Camelot.

19:27.208 --> 19:30.586
-Do you want me to look like a fool?
-I'm going to make you see that Tristan's wrong.

19:30.753 --> 19:35.049
You aren't just anyone. You are special.
You and you alone can draw out that sword.

19:43.307 --> 19:44.850
You'd better be right about this.

20:25.599 --> 20:27.101
You have to believe, Arthur.

20:27.601 --> 20:29.019
[EXHALING]

20:34.984 --> 20:37.194
[PANTING]

20:42.533 --> 20:45.119
You're destined to be Albion's greatest king.

20:47.747 --> 20:51.083
Nothing, not even this stone,
can stand in your way.

21:09.769 --> 21:11.520
Have faith.

21:43.302 --> 21:44.512
Long live the king!

21:44.678 --> 21:48.516
ALL: Long live the king!
Long live the king!

21:48.682 --> 21:52.144
Long live the king!
Long live the king!

21:52.895 --> 21:54.522
Long live the king!

21:59.276 --> 22:02.071
When they arrived there,
the ground itself was still on fire.

22:02.238 --> 22:04.406
They'd all been slaughtered,
every last one of them.

22:04.573 --> 22:05.866
And Agravaine?

22:07.076 --> 22:08.619
Dead.

22:08.786 --> 22:10.996
There's only one person
who could have done this.

22:11.956 --> 22:14.667
Only one man
who could command a dragon.

22:18.128 --> 22:19.880
This is the work of Emrys.

22:23.008 --> 22:26.345
-What about the drawbridge?
-Well-manned. As are the northern gates.

22:26.512 --> 22:27.888
The battlements on the south side?

22:28.055 --> 22:30.766
Arthur, even if we can get inside,
she has an army.

22:30.933 --> 22:33.102
And we have what-- Few hundred?

22:33.269 --> 22:35.980
-And they still outnumber us.
-Yeah, but only 3-to-1.

22:36.605 --> 22:39.149
-And do you think they'll fight?
-They'll fight for Arthur.

22:39.316 --> 22:41.944
It's not for me they have to fight for.
It's for Camelot.

22:42.111 --> 22:44.822
No, Arthur.
It is you the people love...

22:44.989 --> 22:47.908
...and you that they will lay down
their lives for.

22:48.409 --> 22:51.161
| know that I would ride
into the mouth of hell for you.

22:53.455 --> 22:54.999
And I.

23:00.254 --> 23:01.380
And I.

23:12.308 --> 23:13.851
Then to the mouth of hell it is.

23:26.488 --> 23:27.990
What's this for?

23:38.375 --> 23:40.044
Never give up hope.

23:41.670 --> 23:43.714
Love is stronger than anything.

23:45.007 --> 23:46.634
Believe me.

23:56.852 --> 23:58.187
You all right?

23:58.938 --> 24:00.314
Yes.

24:01.482 --> 24:03.609
Do you think
there are too many of them?

24:04.652 --> 24:07.029
The Southrons are men like you and me.

24:07.196 --> 24:08.739
Men we can fight.

24:09.615 --> 24:11.533
But Morgana...

24:12.701 --> 24:16.288
...her power is so great,
and we've got nothing to answer it with.

24:17.539 --> 24:20.918
- I never finished Gaius's story.
-Not now, Merlin. Please.

24:21.085 --> 24:22.336
Will you just listen?

24:25.839 --> 24:28.634
When the sword
was thrust into the stone...

24:28.801 --> 24:31.929
...the ancient king foretold
that one day it would be freed again...

24:32.096 --> 24:34.556
...at a time when Camelot
needed it most.

24:34.723 --> 24:37.434
The man who freed it would
unite the land of Albion...

24:37.643 --> 24:40.771
...and rule over the greatest kingdom
the world has ever known.

24:42.564 --> 24:43.899
That man is you, Arthur.

24:49.697 --> 24:50.781
You're making this up.

24:50.948 --> 24:53.575
Why would I do that?
Your head's already as big as your waist.

24:53.742 --> 24:55.369
| believe it though.

24:56.328 --> 24:57.788
And I believe in you.

25:00.165 --> 25:01.667
| always have.

25:33.866 --> 25:35.826
[SPEAKING IN ANCIENT LANGUAGE]

25:40.956 --> 25:42.750
[GROANS]

25:46.086 --> 25:48.213
MORGANA:
We must send emissaries to Lot's kingdom.

25:48.380 --> 25:50.716
We must offer a reward for Arthur's capture.

25:52.092 --> 25:54.261
It's him. It's Emrys. He's here.

25:54.428 --> 25:56.055
Guards!

26:15.365 --> 26:17.576
[SPEAKING IN ANCIENT LANGUAGE]

26:22.790 --> 26:24.541
[ VOICES WHISPERING]

26:27.377 --> 26:28.420
[CHUCKLES]

26:28.587 --> 26:30.339
[BELLS TOLLING]

26:44.436 --> 26:46.897
We've searched everywhere.
He fled, Morgana.

26:47.064 --> 26:48.732
He trembled at the sight of you.

26:48.899 --> 26:51.568
Why was he here?
Why does he choose to taunt me like this?

26:51.735 --> 26:53.862
We must hold our nerve.

26:55.572 --> 26:57.658
Maybe you should get some sleep.

27:08.335 --> 27:09.920
Make sure there are guards on the door.

27:32.734 --> 27:35.237
[VOICES WHISPERING]

27:43.662 --> 27:45.414
ARTHUR:
Wakey, wakey.

27:47.207 --> 27:49.209
You look like you've
been up half the night.

27:49.376 --> 27:50.752
| was. Couldn't sleep.

27:51.587 --> 27:53.714
| thought you said you had faith in me.

27:54.423 --> 27:55.924
Whatever gave you that idea?

28:02.681 --> 28:03.932
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

28:04.099 --> 28:05.309
Over there.

28:10.439 --> 28:12.482
This is where we say good-bye.

28:12.649 --> 28:14.067
TRISTAN:
Arthur.

28:14.234 --> 28:17.696
All my life, I've shied away
from other people's wars...

28:17.863 --> 28:24.119
...and despised the power and wealth
that kings buy with the lives of men.

28:25.329 --> 28:27.956
But you've shown yourself to be different.

28:28.624 --> 28:32.169
You've shown us that you fight for
what is right and fair.

28:33.086 --> 28:34.504
And for that reason...

28:35.422 --> 28:37.883
...we would like to fight at your side.

28:42.888 --> 28:44.932
I'd be honored to have you at my side.

28:46.475 --> 28:48.435
We'll stand together as equals.

29:01.740 --> 29:03.033
Arthur?

29:04.117 --> 29:05.953
If anything happens to us,
| want you to know--

29:06.119 --> 29:08.413
-Guinevere--
-I understand why you can't forgive me.

29:08.580 --> 29:10.791
But I never once stopped loving you.

29:10.958 --> 29:12.668
Never once.

30:19.735 --> 30:20.777
[GRUNTS]

30:34.624 --> 30:36.668
[THUMPS THEN GROANS]

31:03.403 --> 31:05.655
[BELLS TOLLING]

31:19.294 --> 31:20.462
[GRUNTS]

31:25.759 --> 31:28.178
-It seems we have company.
-Emrys.

31:28.345 --> 31:29.429
Arthur.

31:31.431 --> 31:33.225
My dear brother.

31:34.142 --> 31:35.602
We must welcome him home.

31:37.396 --> 31:38.939
Shall we?

31:41.483 --> 31:43.151
[VOICES WHISPERING]

31:58.834 --> 32:02.087
It is as we expected.
He is making his way here.

32:02.629 --> 32:04.756
He should be with us soon.

32:04.923 --> 32:06.591
And we'll be waiting.

32:12.389 --> 32:14.224
[YELLS]

32:35.036 --> 32:36.621
[KEYS JANGLING] ]

32:40.125 --> 32:43.670
Come on, boys.
What's taken you so long?

32:52.512 --> 32:54.264
You all right?

32:54.431 --> 32:57.017
I've been locked up with Gwaine for a week.

33:03.315 --> 33:04.983
Gaius.

33:07.110 --> 33:08.904
All right, come on.

33:09.613 --> 33:11.406
[MEN YELLING IN DISTANCE]

33:12.449 --> 33:14.868
One each. Pick your man.

33:15.452 --> 33:17.162
On me!

33:24.294 --> 33:26.338
[MEN SHOUTING
AND SWORDS CLANGING IN DISTANCE]

33:26.505 --> 33:28.006
I'm going to enjoy this.

33:32.302 --> 33:35.847
Whatever happened to the idea
of finding a bit of land and settling down?

33:36.014 --> 33:39.726
-You know, this thing's not bad.
-Thought you might like it.

33:42.229 --> 33:43.813
Ready?

33:45.815 --> 33:48.777
ALL: For the love of Camelot!
For the love of Camelot!

33:51.488 --> 33:52.864
Welcome, dear brother.

33:53.573 --> 33:55.367
It's been far too long.

33:57.494 --> 33:59.579
| apologize if you had a difficult reception.

34:00.539 --> 34:02.541
It's hard to know who to trust these days.

34:19.306 --> 34:20.850
What happened to you, Morgana?

34:23.603 --> 34:25.563
| thought we were friends.

34:28.525 --> 34:30.025
As did I.

34:32.404 --> 34:34.447
But alas, we were both wrong.

34:35.782 --> 34:37.576
You can't blame me for my father's sins.

34:39.119 --> 34:40.954
It's a little late for that.

34:41.621 --> 34:44.206
You've made it perfectly clear
how you feel about me and my kind.

34:45.875 --> 34:48.128
You're not as different from Uther
as you'd like to think.

34:48.295 --> 34:49.795
Nor are you.

34:53.632 --> 34:56.928
I'm going to enjoy killing you,
Arthur Pendragon.

34:58.305 --> 35:00.098
Not even Emrys can save you now.

35:05.437 --> 35:07.606
Your blades cannot stop me.

35:10.734 --> 35:12.569
[SPEAKS IN ANCIENT LANGUAGE]

35:13.194 --> 35:15.155
[VOICES WHISPERING]

35:22.370 --> 35:23.663
[SPEAKS IN ANCIENT LANGUAGE]

35:24.205 --> 35:25.874
[VOICES WHISPERING]

35:32.047 --> 35:33.548
Not so powerful now, my lady.

35:41.097 --> 35:42.682
After her!

35:49.522 --> 35:51.816
[GRUNTING]

36:45.620 --> 36:47.872
[GRUNTING]

36:51.501 --> 36:52.752
[GROANS]

36:55.922 --> 36:57.257
[YELLS]

37:13.857 --> 37:15.734
[SWORD SLICES]

37:16.776 --> 37:18.611
[SWORD SLICES]

37:49.392 --> 37:51.603
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

38:10.580 --> 38:12.957
What did I do to make you
hate me so much?

38:13.124 --> 38:15.710
It's not what you did.
It's what you're destined to do.

38:16.836 --> 38:19.255
And I'm sorry, Gwen,
but I can never let that happen.

38:32.477 --> 38:34.229
[RUMBLING]

38:42.403 --> 38:44.531
-Are you all right?
-Yes.

38:47.450 --> 38:49.118
What happened?

38:56.751 --> 38:58.461
| don't know.

39:09.514 --> 39:12.308
-I'm sorry.
-Shh.

39:13.226 --> 39:14.686
Our dreams.

39:14.853 --> 39:16.938
Isolde, don't.

39:18.064 --> 39:20.608
ISOLDE: I wish--
TRISTAN: I wish too.

39:26.739 --> 39:28.408
Hold me.

40:14.370 --> 40:16.247
[BELLS TOLLING]

40:22.045 --> 40:23.546
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACH]

40:27.258 --> 40:28.760
It will take some time.

40:29.969 --> 40:31.846
Merlin can take care of it.

40:36.017 --> 40:38.227
If you want me to go,
to return to Ealdor--

40:38.394 --> 40:39.562
| want you to stay.

40:43.733 --> 40:45.568
-Guinevere--
-You don't have to say anything.

40:45.735 --> 40:47.987
-Whatever's happened between us--
-I can't forgive myself.

40:48.154 --> 40:49.697
| don't care.

40:53.785 --> 40:55.995
| just don't ever want to lose you.

41:12.345 --> 41:13.805
Will you marry me?

41:15.848 --> 41:16.891
Yes.

41:18.643 --> 41:20.687
Yes, with all my heart.

42:07.650 --> 42:10.445
By the sacred laws vested in me...

42:12.447 --> 42:13.698
...crown you...

42:15.033 --> 42:16.993
...Guinevere...

42:19.704 --> 42:21.330
...queen of Camelot.

42:57.116 --> 42:58.868
Long live the queen!

42:59.035 --> 43:01.162
ALL:
Long live the queen!

43:01.329 --> 43:03.081
Long live the queen!

43:03.956 --> 43:05.708
Long live the queen!

43:06.250 --> 43:07.960
Long live the queen!

43:08.419 --> 43:10.421
Long live the queen!

43:13.424 --> 43:15.468
[PANTING]

43:28.564 --> 43:30.274
[GROANS]

43:38.241 --> 43:39.909
[EXHALES]

43:50.753 --> 43:52.713
[WINGS FLAPPING]

43:56.968 --> 43:58.678
[CHITTERING]

44:01.931 --> 44:04.100
[HISSES]

44:39.093 --> 44:40.720
MAN:
Merlin.

